/* Passengers */1) There is no officially accepted term as "temporary" flight. Flights can either be classified as 'scheduled/commercial', 'unscheduled/special', 'Charter', 'Repartition'  or 'Rescue' flights. 

2) This flight is directly classified under 'scheduled/commercial' due to-
   A) This flight appears under official schedule/booking engine of respective airline. 
   B) Anyone can book this flight without giving any prior information to Embassy/High Commission of either of countries....

/* Passenger */Flight tracking websites are not reliable sources. To avoid edit war, You can put views here for consensus- https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Kempegowda_International_Airport#Reliable_Sources

/* Passenger */First of all, if a destination is present for a long time, It never does imply that it gets the right to remain as it is permanent especially when it is unsourced.\n\nSecondly, Flight tracking websites like Flightaware.com is not a [[reliable source]]
